By their nature, interactive kiosks require robust 
and secure kiosk hardware and software to ensure a 
consistent user experience and prevent unauthorized 
modification. A number of kiosk manufacturers offer 
this type of solution, but quality and features can 
vary widely between vendors. When evaluating 
interactive kiosk manufacturers, be sure to ask 
about their quality assurance process, warranty coverage, 
and method for handling situations such as dusty or 
humid operating environments. You may also wish to 
identify a reliable kiosk service and support 
organization for your interactive kiosk project.
